## Content Quality Standards

### Google Helpful Content Alignment

The Helpful Content Update rewards content that:

| Criterion | Our Implementation |
|-----------|-------------------|
| Created for people, not search engines | Intent-first architecture, answer user questions immediately |
| Demonstrates expertise | Location-specific knowledge, genuine service details |
| Has a primary purpose | Each page has clear goal (inform, convert, navigate) |
| Provides satisfying experience | Fast to scan, easy to convert, mobile-optimized |
| Avoids thin content | Word count targets in Content Specifications |
| No excessive automation | Human review of all content |

### Content Quality Checklist

Before publishing any page:

- [ ] Does the content immediately address what users searching this keyword want?
- [ ] Would someone recommend this page to a friend looking for this service?
- [ ] Is there unique information not available on competitor pages?
- [ ] Does the page answer the user's question without them needing to search again?
- [ ] Is the content written in natural language, not keyword-stuffed?
- [ ] Does the page provide clear next steps (CTA)?

