## Technical SEO Requirements

### Intent-to-URL Ownership (Critical)

- City head terms must resolve to city pages, not homepage (example: `escort amsterdam` -> `/escort-amsterdam/`).
- District terms must resolve to district pages (example: `escort amsterdam centrum` -> `/escort-amsterdam-centrum/`).
- Homepage may support city terms, but must not be the canonical target for those terms.
- Avoid redirects that collapse specific city intent into `/`.

### Page-Level Requirements

| Element | Requirement |
|---------|-------------|
| **Title tag** | 50-60 chars, primary keyword front-loaded |
| **Meta description** | 150-160 chars, includes CTA and differentiator |
| **H1** | Exactly one per page, contains primary keyword |
| **URL** | Lowercase, hyphens, descriptive, no parameters |
| **Canonical** | Self-referencing for all indexable pages |
| **Robots** | `index, follow` for all public pages |

### Schema Markup Requirements

| Page Type | Required Schema |
|-----------|-----------------|
| Homepage | Organization, LocalBusiness |
| Location pages | LocalBusiness (per location), FAQPage |
| Attribute pages | FAQPage |
| Service pages | Service, FAQPage |
| Profile pages | Person, Review (if applicable) |
| Blog posts | Article, FAQPage (if FAQ present), Person (author) |

### Schema Implementation Example

**FAQ Schema** (required on most pages):

```json
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Hoe snel kan een escort bij mij zijn in Amsterdam?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Binnen 90 minuten in heel Amsterdam. Gemiddelde wachttijd in het centrum is 45-60 minuten."
      }
    }
  ]
}
```

**LocalBusiness Schema** (location pages):

```json
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "LocalBusiness",
  "name": "Desire Escorts Amsterdam",
  "description": "High-class escort service in Amsterdam",
  "areaServed": {
    "@type": "City",
    "name": "Amsterdam"
  },
  "priceRange": "€€€"
}
```

### Hreflang Implementation

For NL/EN bilingual pages:

```html
<link rel="alternate" hreflang="nl" href="https://desire-escorts.nl/escort-amsterdam" />
<link rel="alternate" hreflang="en" href="https://desire-escorts.nl/en/escort-amsterdam" />
<link rel="alternate" hreflang="x-default" href="https://desire-escorts.nl/escort-amsterdam" />
```

**Rules**:
- NL pages under `/`
- EN pages under `/en/`
- `x-default` points to NL version
- Every NL page must have EN alternate and vice versa

