## Internal Linking Strategy

### Link Preservation from Legacy

During migration, preserve internal links that:
- Connect location pages to profiles
- Connect attribute pages to relevant profiles
- Link between related services
- Create hub-and-spoke structure from homepage

### New Linking Patterns

| From | To | Purpose |
|------|-----|---------|
| Homepage | Top 5 location pages | Primary navigation |
| Homepage | Main attribute pages | Category navigation |
| Location pages | Profile pages (filtered) | Conversion pathway |
| Location pages | Nearby location pages | Related content |
| Attribute pages | Location pages with that attribute | Cross-linking |
| Blog posts | Relevant service/location pages | Contextual links |

### Anchor Text Guidelines

| Pattern | Example | Use Case |
|---------|---------|----------|
| Exact match | "escort amsterdam" | Sparingly, only if natural |
| Partial match | "onze escorts in Amsterdam" | Preferred |
| Branded | "Bekijk ons aanbod" | For CTAs |
| Natural | "in de hoofdstad" | Contextual |

**Avoid**:
- Over-optimized anchor text
- "Click here" or generic anchors
- Excessive links (>3-5 per 500 words)

