## Mobile & Performance Optimization

### Mobile-First Requirements

- All content scannable on mobile viewport
- CTAs thumb-friendly and visible without scrolling
- Images optimized and lazy-loaded
- No horizontal scrolling
- Text readable without zooming (16px minimum)

### Core Web Vitals Targets

| Metric | Target |
|--------|--------|
| LCP (Largest Contentful Paint) | <2.5s |
| INP (Interaction to Next Paint) | <200ms |
| CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift) | <0.1 |

### Performance Guidelines

- Optimize images (WebP, responsive sizes)
- Minimize third-party scripts
- Use static generation where possible
- Implement caching headers
- Defer non-critical JavaScript

---

## Content Freshness Strategy

### Freshness Signals for AI Systems

AI systems and Google favor fresh content:

- **Last updated dates**: Display prominently on informational content
- **Recent availability**: Show real-time or daily-updated availability status
- **News/blog**: Regular publishing cadence (minimum 2x monthly)
- **Seasonal updates**: Refresh location pages with seasonal info

### Update Triggers

| Trigger | Action |
|---------|--------|
| New escort joins | Update relevant location/attribute pages |
| Price change | Update service and pricing pages |
| Service change | Update service pages |
| Monthly | Review and refresh top 10 traffic pages |
| Quarterly | Full content audit of commercial pages |

